2004/05.punditry: Ranelagh won their first Women's Division 1 title in the league's 26-year history, holding off defending champions Belgrave despite the Belles winning two of the four matches.

2006/07.punditry: Belgrave's Chrissie Wellington, fresh from winning the World Triathlon Age Group Championships, won Race 2 at Lightwater with teammate Catherine Bryson second - the Belles' first 1-2 in years. The following year Wellington would win the first of her four Ironman World Championships.

2025/26.punditry: [BEL](@club:BEL) claimed their third consecutive title, completing the historic double with the men's team – only the second time this has been achieved.
